08/12/2004
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The government of Republika Srpska (RS) announced on Tuesday (7 December) that it would pay 25,000 euros to the family of every war crimes indictee who turns himself in by the end of the year.
Each suspect and his family would also receive monthly payments of 690 euros, as well as four return tickets to The Hague.
Children would be entitled to free schooling.
(Tanjug, Nezavisne novine, Danas - 08/12/04;
Reuters, AFP, PBS BiH, Fena - 07/12/04)
